'''Project Cost Management (PCM)''' is a method that uses technology to measure cost and productivity through the full life cycle of enterprise level projects.{{Citation needed|date=July 2010}}

PCM encompasses several specific functions of [[project management]] including [[Estimation (project management)|estimating]], job controls, field data collection, [[Schedule (project management)|scheduling]], accounting and design.
PCM main goal is to complete a project within an approved budget<ref>{{cite book|last1=College|first1=Kathy Schwalbe, Ph.D., PMP, Augsburg|title=Information technology project management|date=2012|publisher=Course Technology|location=Boston, MA|isbn=9781133526858|edition=Seventh edition.}}</ref>

Beginning with estimating, a vital tool in PCM, actual historical data is used to accurately plan all aspects of the project.
As the project continues, job control uses data from the estimate with the information reported from the field to measure the cost and production in the project. From project initiation to completion, project cost management has an objective to simplify and cheapen the project experience.
<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Project Estimating and Cost Management|author=Rad, P.F.|date=2002|publisher=Management Concepts|isbn=9781567261448|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=GdJgjB5w0KgC|accessdate=2015-09-14}}</ref>

This technological approach has been a big challenger to the mainstream estimating software and project management industries.<ref name="gartner">{{cite web|url=http://www.gartner.com/technology/media-products/reprints/microsoft/vol10/article12/article12.html|title=Magic Quadrant for IT Project and Portfolio Management|publisher=gartner.com|accessdate=2015-09-14}}</ref>
<ref name="twproject">{{cite web|url=https://twproject.com/blog/practical-project-cost-management-with-twproject/|title=Practical Project Cost Management with Twproject &#124; Twproject&#039;s blog|publisher=web.archive.org|accessdate=2015-09-14}}</ref>

